2026 Regular Session
HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 374
BY REPRESENTATIVE FIRMENT
WATER/RESOURCES: Urges and requests the Department of Wildlife and Fisheries and
the Department of Conservation and Energy to study cooperative endeavor
agreements for the withdrawal of surface water
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To urge and request the Department of Wildlife and Fisheries and the Department of
3 Conservation and Energy to study cooperative endeavor agreements for the
4 withdrawal of surface water and provide a written summary of their findings to the
5 House Committee on Natural Resources and Environment prior to the convening of
6 the 2027 Regular Session of the Legislature.
7 WHEREAS, the House of Representatives of the Legislature of Louisiana finds and
8 declares that the surface waters of the state of Louisiana are among its most valuable natural
9 resources and are essential to the state's economy, environment, public safety, and quality
10 of life; and
11 WHEREAS, the House of Representatives of the Legislature of Louisiana further
12 finds that the responsible management of surface water resources requires a balanced
13 approach that supports economic development while ensuring the long-term sustainability
14 and usability of the state's waterways; and
15 WHEREAS, the House of Representatives of the Legislature of Louisiana recognizes
16 that invasive aquatic vegetation and species including but not limited to giant salvinia, water
17 hyacinth, and hydrilla pose a significant and growing threat to Louisiana's lakes, rivers, and
18 other water bodies by impairing navigation, increasing flood risk, degrading wildlife habitat,
19 and limiting public access; and
