1 WHEREAS, the House of Representatives of the Legislature of Louisiana further
2 finds that aquatic vegetation overgrowth and invasive species infestations can render water
3 bodies unusable for commerce, recreation, and resource management if not effectively
4 controlled; and
5 WHEREAS, the House of Representatives of the Legislature of Louisiana intends
6 to:
7 (1) Ensure that the use and withdrawal of surface water resources contributes to the
8 preservation and maintenance of those resources.
9 (2) Support a statewide, coordinated approach to aquatic vegetation management and
10 invasive species control.
11 (3) Provide for research, monitoring, and long-term management strategies to
12 address invasive aquatic species.
13 (4) Establish sustainable funding mechanisms to assist in the protection and
14 restoration of Louisiana's waterways for the benefit of present and future generations.
15 THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the House of Representatives of the
16 Legislature of Louisiana does hereby urge and request the Department of Wildlife and
17 Fisheries and the Department of Conservation and Energy to study cooperative endeavor
18 agreements for the withdrawal of surface water including consideration of the four
19 enumerated intentions of the House of Representatives as expressed in this Resolution and
20 provide a written summary of their findings to the House Committee on Natural Resources
21 and Environment at least thirty days prior to the convening of the 2027 Regular Session of
22 the Legislature.
23 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that a copy of this Resolution be transmitted to the
24 secretary of the Department of Wildlife and Fisheries and the secretary of the Department
25 of Conservation and Energy.
